                <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/106: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul in Charge of the Legation in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lawton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-12-11T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 11, 1919, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your December 4, 11 A.M., and Department’s Dec. 1, 2 P.M., inform Government of
                    Honduras that Department considers the installing of telegraph lines in the
                    disputed territory a violation of the <hi rend="italic">status quo</hi> and such
                    lines should therefore be removed. The Department has telegraphed Legation at
                    Managua to take up with Nicaraguan Government question of cutting timber in
                    disputed territory.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
